cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper is about training neural networks on image datasets, which is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a topic in the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the algorithm proposed in the paper is adaptive and parameterless, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
